<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="136" pageId="3" pageNumber="135" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1516,2010]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,645]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="136" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,365,1516,1541]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Redescription</emphasis>
. (
<specimenCount box="[391,413,1517,1541]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
) Body length 6.5–7.0 mm. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[735,818,1516,1541]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Colour</emphasis>
. Body integument brownish black; vestiture of elytra consisting of short, rounded, recumbent, overlapping scales, slightly longer that wide, concealing integument in fresh specimens, forming shades of whitish yellow and brownish colour, basal and apical thirds of elytra paler, medium third with a darker transverse band. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[699,762,1625,1650]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Head</emphasis>
. Rostrum longer than head plus prothorax, thin, evenly narrowing from base to insertion of antennae, sides parallel in apical half, moderately downcurved, punctate and covered by scales in basal third, smooth and shiny in medium and apical thirds, transverse furrow at base of rostrum reduced, concealed by scales, head short; antennae with segments 1 and 2 subequal in length, 1 as long as 3+4. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[210,332,1769,1794]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Prothorax</emphasis>
. Wider than long, widest and rounded in apical third, sides almost straight in basal half, densely punctate, median line present, visible through scales, scales brown with paler spots on sides. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1191,1267,1805,1830]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Elytra</emphasis>
. Twice as long as wide (ratio w/l: 0.55), sides subparallel in basal two thirds, rounded in apical third, humeri raised, declivital callosities present at apex of interstria 3, followed by a strong depression, striae narrow, interstriae flat and wide; scutellum small, shiny and flat. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[511,627,1913,1938]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Underside covered by pale brownish scales, ventrites 1 and 2 elongate and subequal, 2 as long as 3–5. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[503,559,1949,1974]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Legs</emphasis>
. Femora clavate, armed with a strong ventral tooth; tibiae straight, armed with a strong ventral tooth proximally near middle; tarsi reddish. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[839,949,1985,2010]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Genitalia</emphasis>
. Penis short (ratio w/l: 0.5), sides straight, subparallel, converging near apex, apex truncate, slightly and regularly curved in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1230,1322,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1565,1587]" captionTargetBox="[189,1409,396,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,373,1544]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 6. Penis of Afrosmicronyx species, dorsal (left) and lateral (right) view. A. Afrosmicronyx giganteus (Hustache), specimen from Cameroon. B. A. quadrituberculatus (Hustache), lectotype. C. A. sopubiae (Marshall), lectotype. D. A. angolanus (Hustache), holotype. E. A. maerens (Marshall), lectotype. F. A. dorsomaculatus (Cox), specimen from Mauritania. G. A.mirei sp.n., holotype.H.A.armipes (Voss),holotype.I. A.madagascariensis sp. n., holotype.J.A.umbrinus (Hustache), specimen from Cameroon.Scale bar = 200 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1117518/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">
Fig. 6 
<collectingRegion box="[1299,1322,151,176]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">A</collectingRegion>
</figureCitation>
). Females are distinguished from males by their slightly longer ventral tooth on tibiae, by their rostrum, which is less coarsely punctate in apical half, and by the insertion of their antennae on rostrum, which nearer to middle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,645]" box="[199,883,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,336,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Life history</emphasis>
. Unknown. Adults collected in July and August.
</paragraph>
