<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="136" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,332,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Discussion</emphasis>
. Hustache’s description of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hustache" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[633,913,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis box="[633,913,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Afrosmicronyx giganteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was based on a single specimen, from Sokolo (“ 
<collectingCountry box="[169,244,367,392]" name="Sudan" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Sudan</collectingCountry>
” [
<collectingCountry box="[270,330,367,392]" name="Serbia" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Mali</collectingCountry>
], 
<date box="[349,447,367,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136" value="1933-07">vii-1933</date>
, Hustache 1935). This species is by far the largest of the genus and cannot be confused with any other species. Despite intensive search, the specimen used by Hustache for the description of the species was not found in the 
<collectionCode box="[413,498,440,463]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">MNHN</collectionCode>
collections. However, in the Rema.coll there is a specimen from Dogo (
<collectingCountry box="[1373,1429,439,464]" name="Serbia" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Mali</collectingCountry>
) identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haran &amp; Perrin" authorityYear="2017" box="[302,419,477,500]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Smicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[302,419,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Smicronyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[438,661,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">
s. g. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hustache" authorityYear="1935" box="[498,661,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Afrosmicronyx</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
) 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hustache" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[680,789,477,500]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis box="[680,789,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">giganteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<collectingRegion box="[837,860,476,500]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">A</collectingRegion>
. Hoffmann, with the indication “comparison with 
<typeStatus box="[151,204,512,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">type</typeStatus>
”. 
<collectingRegion box="[225,248,512,536]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">A</collectingRegion>
. Hoffmann has created confusions by transferring several 
<typeStatus box="[896,955,512,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">types</typeStatus>
of Hustache to his collection (
<bibRefCitation author="Perrin" box="[1294,1428,511,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136" refString="Perrin, H. (1998) Les types des especes afrotropicales du genre Curculio Linne, 1758 (Coleoptera, Curculionidae). Revue francaise d'Entomologie, 20 (4), 135 - 141." type="journal article" year="1998">Perrin 1998</bibRefCitation>
) and relabeling them. But since this specimen was found in the Rema.coll it is not likely a transfer of 
<collectingRegion box="[1287,1310,548,572]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">A</collectingRegion>
. Hoffmann in this case. In the absence of available 
<typeStatus box="[592,640,584,608]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">type</typeStatus>
material, and given the need to provide a 
<typeStatus box="[1108,1156,584,608]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">type</typeStatus>
for this nominal species, we designated this specimen as the 
<typeStatus box="[549,638,621,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">neotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hustache" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[675,954,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis box="[675,954,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="136">Afrosmicronyx giganteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
